The NASA Summit has unanimously endorsed NASA Founder and ANC Party leader Musalia Mudavadi to be the Chairman of NASA National Campaign Committee (NACACO). The endorsement follows a proposal to the Summit by NASA flag bearer Raila Odinga.The NASA Summit comprises of the party leaders of the five anchor parties ANC Mudavadi, ODM Raila, Wiper Kalonzo Musyoka, Ford-Kenya Moses Wetangula and Chama Cha Mashinani (CCM) Isaac Ruto.The NASA Summit has unanimously endorsed NASA founder and ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi (pictured) to be the chairman of NASA National Campaign Committee The endorsement follows a proposal to the summit by NASA flagbearer Raila Odinga.The summit comprises leaders of the five anchor parties namely Mudavadi, ODM&rsquo;s Raila, Kalonzo Musyoka of Wiper, Ford Kenya&rsquo;s Moses Wetang&rsquo;ula and Isaac Rutto of Chama Cha Mashinani.NACACO is the apex campaign decision-making body that will coordinate NASA presidential campaign and overall NASA campaign machinery. Modelled on the USA&rsquo;s Democratic Party National Committee, Mudavadi will preside over high level research and strategy team of experts, communications, resource mobilisation, operations and logistics, supported by a 24-hour secretariat.Mudavadi will head a NACACO team of 10 people, seconded by the partner parties, to oversee a massive structure that runs through and is replicated in 47 County Campaign Coordinating Committees, 290 constituencies, 1,450 wards and 40,000 polling stations. Mudavadi&rsquo;s role is in line with the NASA power-sharing formula where he will be the Premier Cabinet Secretar, akin to a premier.&ldquo;I have graciously accepted to play this pivotal role because I believe a win for NASA is a win for Kenyans,&rdquo; Mudavadi told his ANC Strategy team on Thursday.